    "fastsim.jit": {
      "name": "fastsim.jit",
      "description": "",
      "docstring_html": "",
      "classes": [],
      "functions": [
        {
          "name": "jit",
          "description": "Trace and compile a Python function to optimized Rust IR.",
          "docstring_html": "<p>Trace and compile a Python function to optimized Rust IR.</p>\n<p>The returned callable evaluates the function in Rust with zero Python\noverhead per call. Tracing is lazy by default (on first call) or eager\nif <tt class=\"docutils literal\">n_x</tt> is provided.</p>\n<p>Supported operations: arithmetic, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\">np.sin/cos/tan/exp/log/tanh/...</span></tt>,\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\">np.dot</tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\">np.clip</tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\">np.where</tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\">np.linalg.norm</tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\">np.cross</tt>,\nmatrix multiply (<tt class=\"docutils literal\">&#64;</tt>), <tt class=\"docutils literal\">np.sum</tt>, and more. Unsupported patterns fall\nback to the original Python function.</p>\n<p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>\n<dl class=\"docutils\">\n<dt>func <span class=\"classifier-delimiter\">:</span> <span class=\"classifier\">callable</span></dt>\n<dd>Python function with signature <tt class=\"docutils literal\">f(x)</tt> or <tt class=\"docutils literal\">f(x, t)</tt> where\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\">x</tt> is a list/array of floats and <tt class=\"docutils literal\">t</tt> is a scalar.</dd>\n<dt>n_x <span class=\"classifier-delimiter\">:</span> <span class=\"classifier\">int, optional</span></dt>\n<dd>Input dimension. If provided, the function is traced eagerly\nat construction time. Otherwise tracing is deferred to the\nfirst call, where <tt class=\"docutils literal\">n_x</tt> is inferred from the input length.</dd>\n</dl>\n<p><strong>Returns</strong></p>\n<dl class=\"docutils\">\n<dt>compiled <span class=\"classifier-delimiter\">:</span> <span class=\"classifier\">JitFunction</span></dt>\n<dd>Callable that evaluates the traced function in Rust.</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"example\">\n<h4>Example</h4>\n<pre class=\"code python literal-block\">\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">fastsim.jit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">jit</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">numpy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">np</span><span class=\"w\">\n\n</span><span class=\"k\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">f</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">):</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span>    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">np</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">])</span> <span class=\"o\">+</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">np</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">exp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">])]</span><span class=\"w\">\n\n</span><span class=\"n\">f_fast</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">jit</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span><span class=\"n\">result</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">f_fast</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">2.0</span><span class=\"p\">],</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># numpy array</span><span class=\"w\">\n\n</span><span class=\"c1\"># Eager compilation</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span><span class=\"n\">f_fast</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">jit</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">n_x</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n",
          "source": null,
          "signature": "(func, n_x = None)",
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "func",
              "type": null,
              "default": null,
              "description": "Python function with signature ``f(x)`` or ``f(x, t)`` where ``x`` is a list/array of floats and ``t`` is a scalar."
            },
            {
              "name": "n_x",
              "type": null,
              "default": "None",
              "description": "Input dimension. If provided, the function is traced eagerly at construction time. Otherwise tracing is deferred to the first call, where ``n_x`` is inferred from the input length."
            }
          ],
          "returns": null
        },
        {
          "name": "jacobian",
          "description": "Compute the Jacobian of a Python function via symbolic automatic",
          "docstring_html": "<p>Compute the Jacobian of a Python function via symbolic automatic\ndifferentiation.</p>\n<p>The returned callable evaluates the full Jacobian matrix in Rust.\nDifferentiation is performed symbolically on the traced computation\ngraph — no finite differences, no tape replay. The Jacobian graph\nis optimized (constant folding, CSE) before evaluation.</p>\n<p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>\n<dl class=\"docutils\">\n<dt>func <span class=\"classifier-delimiter\">:</span> <span class=\"classifier\">callable</span></dt>\n<dd>Python function with signature <tt class=\"docutils literal\">f(x)</tt> or <tt class=\"docutils literal\">f(x, t)</tt> where\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\">x</tt> is a list/array of floats and <tt class=\"docutils literal\">t</tt> is a scalar.\nMust return a list/array of floats.</dd>\n<dt>n_x <span class=\"classifier-delimiter\">:</span> <span class=\"classifier\">int, optional</span></dt>\n<dd>Input dimension. If provided, the function is traced eagerly.\nOtherwise tracing is deferred to the first call.</dd>\n</dl>\n<p><strong>Returns</strong></p>\n<dl class=\"docutils\">\n<dt>jac_fn <span class=\"classifier-delimiter\">:</span> <span class=\"classifier\">JitJacobian</span></dt>\n<dd>Callable that returns the Jacobian as a numpy array with shape\n<tt class=\"docutils literal\">(n_out, n_x)</tt>. For scalar functions, returns a scalar.</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"example\">\n<h4>Example</h4>\n<pre class=\"code python literal-block\">\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">fastsim.jit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">jacobian</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">numpy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">np</span><span class=\"w\">\n\n</span><span class=\"k\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">robertson</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">):</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span>    <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">c</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.04</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">1e4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">3e7</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span>    <span class=\"k\">return</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span>             <span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span>             <span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"o\">**</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\">\n\n</span><span class=\"n\">jac_fn</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">jacobian</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">robertson</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">n_x</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span><span class=\"n\">J</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">jac_fn</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"mf\">1.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">],</span> <span class=\"mf\">0.0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">\n</span><span class=\"c1\"># J is a 3x3 numpy array with analytical partial derivatives</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n",
          "source": null,
          "signature": "(func, n_x = None)",
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "func",
              "type": null,
              "default": null,
              "description": "Python function with signature ``f(x)`` or ``f(x, t)`` where ``x`` is a list/array of floats and ``t`` is a scalar. Must return a list/array of floats."
            },
            {
              "name": "n_x",
              "type": null,
              "default": "None",
              "description": "Input dimension. If provided, the function is traced eagerly. Otherwise tracing is deferred to the first call."
            }
          ],
          "returns": null
        }
      ]
